The paper discusses image denoising using multi-layer perceptrons, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the training procedure and trade-offs, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The analysis of the functioning principle of multi-layer perceptrons is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT).
